C1. Sb1 believes that Sb2 has done wrong. C2. Sb1 holds Sb2 in bad stead because of C1. C3. Sb1 decides that this Sb2 should no longer be held in bad stead (despite C1).
The first schema is defined by the broadest most basic set of conditions and should capture most if not all FORGIVE events. The second schema that we
Pmay refer to as GUILTLESS FORGIVE, represents a more criterially complex
yet important part of the cognitive model of forgive
