C4. Sb1 no longer holds Sb2 in bad stead.
ri The GUILTLESS FORGIVE schema should capture events where an individual n is “proven innocent”. In other words, where Sb1 changes opinion on the t validity of C1. It is closely related to another model of FORGIVE, where the
action deemed 'bad' is not serious, often because it is a technicality or is
P considered ‘not serious’ by the person judging the action. r LIGHT FORGIVE e C1. Sb1 believes that Sb2 has done wrong.
C2. Sb1 believes this wrong is not worthy of bad stead.
v C3. Sb1 decides that Sb2 should not be held in bad stead (despite C1). ie Closely related to the concept of FORGIVE is that of APOLOGISE or SORRY.
